labels.label:
This flow demonstrates denormalization. The source data has multiple values for the same column. The flow will denormalize the data, adding redundant data to the record. The flow implements two denormalization types:
- Concatenation - Add new fields

Denormalized Output File - Concatenate Fields
name,month brian,"jan,feb,mar" vincent,"apr,may,jun"
This denormalization process creates duplicates that we need to handle
For Demos, restart the caching service

Normailized Input File:
name,month brian,jan vincent,apr brian,feb vincent,may brian,mar vincent,jun

Denormalized Output File - New Fields
name,month,month1,month2 brian,jan,feb,mar vincent,apr,may,jun

Concatenate new attributes as the value for the month column
/month = ${allMatchingAttributes("denormalized.month.[a-z]*"):join(",")}

Partitioned Output:
name,month vincent,apr vincent,may vincent,jun

Normailized Input File:
name,month brian,jan vincent,apr brian,feb vincent,may brian,mar vincent,jun

Create Attributes for Values to be Denormalized
denormalized.month.jan = jan denormalized.month.feb = feb denormalized.month.mar = mar denormalized.month.apr = apr denormalized.month.may = may denormalized.month.jun = jun

Denormalized Output - New Fields
name,month,month1,month2 brian,jan,feb,mar vincent,apr,may,jun
However, this produces duplicates that we need to handle

Denormalized Output File - Concatenate Fields
name,month brian,"jan,feb,mar" vincent,"apr,may,jun"
However, this produces duplicate records that we need to handle

Partitioned Output:
name,month brian,jan brian,feb brian,mar
For Demos, restart the caching service
